# BLDC Motor Controller

![][image1]

# A BLDC (Brushless DC) motor controller for a 1000W rear motor in an electric rickshaw is a sophisticated electronic device that manages power delivery, logic control, and safety features to ensure smooth acceleration, braking, and reliable operation. 

![][image2]

## **1\. Power and Electrical Specifications**

| Parameter | Typical Value/Range | Notes |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Rated Power | 1000W | Matches motor power for efficient operation |
| Input Voltage | 48V / 60V (common for e-rickshaws) | Some controllers can support 72V |
| Max Current | 55A peak, 8-9A continuous (flat road) | Handles acceleration and load changes[1](https://evshopify.com/product/bldc-motor-controller-1000w-48v-KHWTbf) |
| Controller Wave Type | Trapezoidal (most common), sometimes Sine wave | Affects motor smoothness and noise |
| Efficiency | Up to 97% | High efficiency for longer range[2](https://5.imimg.com/data5/SELLER/Doc/2024/9/451069343/YO/PU/YU/34117014/ev-motors.pdf) |
| Protection Grade | IP65 or higher | Dust and water resistance for vehicle use[1](https://evshopify.com/product/bldc-motor-controller-1000w-48v-KHWTbf) |
| Operating Frequency | 16 kHz – 24 kHz PWM | High-frequency switching for smooth control |

## **2\. Logic Control and Features**

* Microcontroller-Based Logic:  
  Uses an ARM or similar microcontroller for real-time control, monitoring, and safety.  
* Commutation Logic:  
  Six-step (trapezoidal) or FOC commutation based on Hall sensor feedback or sensorless detection.  
* PID Algorithms:  
  Smooth start and speed regulation using PID (Proportional-Integral-Derivative) control.  
* Multiple Modes:  
  High/low speed, forward/reverse, and regenerative braking modes.  
* Protection Features:  
  * Overcurrent, overvoltage, undervoltage, overtemperature protection.  
  * Hall sensor and throttle fault detection.  
  * Battery voltage monitoring and cutoff.  
  * High pedal lockout (prevents sudden acceleration at startup).  
* Communication:  
  CAN, UART, and sometimes Bluetooth for configuration and diagnostics.  
* LED/Error Codes:  
  LED indicators for fault diagnosis and operational status.

## **3\. Pin Configuration and Wiring**

![][image3]

## **Typical Pin/Connector Functions**

| Pin/Connector | Function | Notes |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Power Input | Battery \+ and \- (thick wires) | 48V/60V, high current |
| Motor Phase Output | U, V, W (thick wires) | Connects to motor windings |
| Hall Sensor Input | 5-pin connector (Vcc, GND, Hall A/B/C) | For rotor position feedback |
| Throttle Input | 3-pin (5V, GND, Signal) | Receives analog or PWM throttle signal |
| Brake Input | 2-pin (high voltage or low) | Cuts motor power on activation |
| Ignition/Lock | 2-pin | Turns controller ON/OFF |
| Reverse Input | 2-pin | Switches motor direction |
| Speed Mode | 2-pin | Selects high/low speed |
| Regenerative Brake | 2-pin | Activates energy recovery |
| Communication | CAN/UART/Bluetooth | For diagnostics and configuration |
| Auxiliary Outputs | Headlight, horn, etc. | Optional, for vehicle integration |

Pin lengths and connector types vary by manufacturer but are generally designed for robust, vibration-resistant automotive use. Wires for power and phase outputs are thicker (often 12-14 AWG), while signal wires are thinner (18-22 AWG).

## **4\. Physical and Mechanical Details**

| Parameter | Typical Value/Range | Notes |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Dimensions | \~20cm × 10cm × 4cm | Compact, fits under seat[1](https://evshopify.com/product/bldc-motor-controller-1000w-48v-KHWTbf) |
| Weight | 2.5 kg | Rugged aluminum housing[1](https://evshopify.com/product/bldc-motor-controller-1000w-48v-KHWTbf) |
| Mounting | Panel mount or bracket | Vibration-resistant design |
| Cooling | Aluminum heat sink, sometimes fan | Ensures thermal stability |

## **5\. Key Functional Features**

* Smooth Acceleration:  
  PID and current control algorithms ensure jerk-free starts and stops[2](https://5.imimg.com/data5/SELLER/Doc/2024/9/451069343/YO/PU/YU/34117014/ev-motors.pdf).  
* Regenerative Braking:  
  Converts kinetic energy to electrical energy, increasing range and reducing brake wear.  
* Fault Detection:  
  Real-time error monitoring with LED codes for quick troubleshooting.  
* Configurable Parameters:  
  Current, voltage, speed, and temperature limits can be set via software or Bluetooth.  
* Auto Phase Sequence Detection:  
  Simplifies installation and prevents wiring errors.

## **6\. Example Wiring Diagram (Typical)**

* Power: Battery \+ and \- to controller input.  
* Motor: U, V, W to motor phase wires.  
* Hall Sensors: 5-pin connector to motor’s Hall outputs.  
* Throttle: 3-pin connector to throttle assembly.  
* Brake: 2-pin to brake switch.  
* Ignition: 2-pin to key switch or lock.  
* Reverse: 2-pin to reverse switch.  
* Auxiliary: Optional connections for lights, horn, etc.

## **7\. Advanced Features (on some models)**

* Bluetooth App Configuration:  
  Adjust controller parameters wirelessly.  
* Temperature Derating:  
  Reduces power output if overheating is detected.  
* Anti-theft Lock:  
  Disables motor via remote or key switch.  
* CAN Bus:  
  Integration with vehicle control networks for diagnostics and advanced control.

## **8\. Safety and Compliance**

* Short Circuit Protection  
* Battery Protection (over/under voltage)  
* Thermal Shutdown (typically at 100°C)  
* Reverse Polarity Protection

## **9\. Application in EV Rickshaw**

* Specifically designed for rear-wheel drive, providing high torque for acceleration and hill climbing.  
* Supports both passenger and cargo e-rickshaw configurations.  
* Ensures reliable operation in urban and semi-urban environments.

**10\. Connection in BLDC MOTOR** 

      ![][image4]

## **1\. Power Wires**

| Wire Color | Name | Connection / Function |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Thick Red | Battery Positive (+) | Connect to positive terminal of 48V battery |
| Thick Black | Battery Negative (-) | Connect to negative terminal of battery (ground) |

## **2\. Motor Phase Wires**

| Wire Color | Name | Connection / Function |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Yellow | Phase U | Connect to motor phase U winding |
| Green | Phase V | Connect to motor phase V winding |
| Blue | Phase W | Connect to motor phase W winding |

## **3\. Hall Sensor Wires (5-pin connector)**

| Wire Color | Name | Connection / Function |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Red | Hall Vcc (5V) | Connect to 5V supply from controller |
| Black | Hall Ground | Connect to controller ground |
| Yellow | Hall A | Connect to Hall sensor output A |
| Green | Hall B | Connect to Hall sensor output B |
| Blue | Hall C | Connect to Hall sensor output C |

## **4\. Throttle Wires (3-pin connector)**

| Wire Color | Name | Connection / Function |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Red | \+5V | Connect to 5V supply from controller |
| Black | Ground | Connect to controller ground |
| Green/White | Signal | Connect to throttle signal wire (variable voltage or PWM) |

## **5\. Brake Wires**

| Wire Color | Name | Connection / Function |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Black | Brake Ground | Connect to brake switch ground |
| White | Brake Signal | Connect to brake switch output |

*   
  When brake is applied, these wires short to signal controller to cut motor power and optionally turn on brake light.

## **6\. Key Switch / Ignition Wires**

| Wire Color | Name | Connection / Function |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Red (thin) | Key Switch Power | Connect to ignition key switch (turns controller ON/OFF) |

## **7\. Reverse Wires**

| Wire Color | Name | Connection / Function |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Blue (thin) | Reverse Signal | Connect to reverse switch; shorting these wires reverses motor direction |

## **8\. Speed Mode / High-Low Speed Wires**

| Wire Color | Name | Connection / Function |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Yellow (thin) | Speed Mode Signal | Connect to switch or ground to select high or low speed mode |

## **9\. Brake Light Output**

| Wire Color | Name | Connection / Function |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Red/White | Brake Light Output | Provides battery voltage output to brake light when brake applied |

## **10\. Additional / Auxiliary Wires**

| Wire Color | Name | Connection / Function |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| May include wires for horn, lights, or communication ports (CAN, UART, Bluetooth) depending on controller model. |  |  |

## **Battery \+  \--------\> Controller Red (Power \+)**

## **Battery \-  \--------\> Controller Black (Power \-)**

## **Motor U    \--------\> Controller Yellow (Phase U)**

## **Motor V    \--------\> Controller Green (Phase V)**

## **Motor W    \--------\> Controller Blue (Phase W)**

## **Hall Vcc   \--------\> Controller Red (Hall \+5V)**

## **Hall GND   \--------\> Controller Black (Hall GND)**

## **Hall A    \---------\> Controller Yellow (Hall A)**

## **Hall B    \---------\> Controller Green (Hall B)**

## **Hall C    \---------\> Controller Blue (Hall C)**

## **Throttle \+5V \--------\> Controller Red (Throttle \+5V)**

## **Throttle GND \--------\> Controller Black (Throttle GND)**

## **Throttle Signal \-----\> Controller Green/White (Throttle Signal)**

## **Brake GND  \---------\> Controller Black (Brake GND)**

## **Brake Signal \--------\> Controller White (Brake Signal)**

## **Ignition Key \--------\> Controller Red (Ignition)**

## **Reverse Switch \------\> Controller Blue (Reverse)**

## **Summary Table of Typical Wire Colors and Functions**

| Wire Color | Function | Notes |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Thick Red | Battery \+ | 48V supply |
| Thick Black | Battery \- (Ground) | Common ground |
| Yellow | Motor Phase U | Connect motor phase U |
| Green | Motor Phase V | Connect motor phase V |
| Blue | Motor Phase W | Connect motor phase W |
| Red (Hall) | Hall Sensor \+5V | Power for Hall sensors |
| Black (Hall) | Hall Sensor Ground | Ground for Hall sensors |
| Yellow (Hall) | Hall Sensor A | Rotor position sensor A |
| Green (Hall) | Hall Sensor B | Rotor position sensor B |
| Blue (Hall) | Hall Sensor C | Rotor position sensor C |
| Red (Throttle) | Throttle \+5V | Power for throttle |
| Black (Throttle) | Throttle Ground | Ground for throttle |
| Green/White (Throttle) | Throttle Signal | Variable voltage/PWM throttle |
| Black (Brake) | Brake Ground | Brake switch ground |
| White (Brake) | Brake Signal | Brake switch signal |
| Red (Key switch) | Ignition/Key switch power | Turns controller ON/OFF |
| Blue (Reverse) | Reverse signal | Short to reverse motor direction |
| Yellow (Speed) | Speed mode select | High/Low speed mode |
| Red/White | Brake light output | Powers brake light |
